s that the next generation of synchrotron-based light sources will provide. © 2005 IOP Publishing Ltd.",,"Global warming; Ionosphere; Light sources; Molecular structure; Ozone; Solar radiation; Synchrotron radiation; Biophysics; Ozone depletion; Photo-induced physics; Synchrotron-based light sources; Atmospheric chemistry",,,,,,"Chim, R.Y.L., Kennedy, R.A., Tuckett, R.P., Zhou, W., Jarvis, G.K., Colins, D.J., Hatherly, P.A., (2001) J. Phys. Chem., 105, p. 8403; Edvardsson, D., Baltzer, P., Karlsson, L., Wannberg, B., Holland, D.M.P., Shaw, D.A., (1999) J. Phys. B: At. Mol. Opt. Phys., 32 (11), pp. 2583-2609; Kendall, P.A., Mason, N.J., Buchanan, G.A., Marston, G., Tegeder, P., Dawes, A., Eden, S., Newnham, D.A., (2003) Chem. Phys., 287 (1-2), pp. 137-142; Langer, J., Matt, S., Meinke, M., Tegeder, P., Stamatovic, A., Illenberger, E., (2000) J. Chem. Phys., 113 (24), p. 11063; Lazendorf, E.J., Kummel, A.C., (1996) Geophys. Res. Lett., 23 (12), p. 1521; Limão-Vieira, P., Eden, S., Kendall, P.A., Mason, N.J., Hoffmann, S.V., (2002) Chem. Phys. Lett., 366 (3-4), pp. 343-349; Limão-Vieira, P., Eden, S., Kendall, P.A., Mason, N.J., Giuliani, A., Heinesch, J., Hubin-Franskin, M.-J., Hoffmann, S.V., (2004) Int. J. Mass Spectrom., 233, pp. 335-341; Lu, Q.-B., Madey, T.E., (1999) J. Chem. Phys., 111 (7), p. 2861; Lu, Q.-B., Sanche, L., (2001) Phys. Rev. Lett., 87 (7), p. 078501; Lu, Q.-B., Sanche, L., (2001) Phys. Rev. B, 63, p. 153403; Mason, N.J., Gingell, J.M., Davis, J.A., Zhao, H., Walker, I.C., Siggel, M.R.F., (1996) J. Phys. B: At. Mol. Opt. Phys., 29 (14), pp. 3075-3089; Mason, N.J., Hughes, P., (1998) An Introduction to Environmental Physics; Mason, N.J., Jones, N.C., Kaminski, L., Osborne, B.A., Marston, G., Fernandez, M.A., Walker, I.C., Newnham, D.A., (2001) Int. J. Mass Spectrom., 205 (1-3), pp. 183-196; Shaw, D.A., Holland, D.M.P., MacDonald, M.A., Hopkirk, A., Hayes, M.A., McSweeney, S.M., (1992) Chem. Phys., 163 (3), p. 387; Solomon, S., Burkholder, J.B., Ravi